&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Immunisation Nurse - Band 6 - 37.5 hours&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a senior staff nurse, preferably with a Specialist Community Public Health qualification in either school nursing or health visiting, to work in the Immunisation team to support the Clinical Service Lead (CSL).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate with be able to work with minimal supervision to promote and support the delivery of the childhood immunisation schedule to the eligible cohorts of school aged children as directed by NHS England and Public Health England. Knowledge of the school age vaccination programme and associated data submission would be preferable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be employed by Croydon Health Services NHS Trust and will work across the borough in a variety of settings, including schools, clinics, health centres and the clients homes to deliver immunisations. You will work with the CSL and wider team to improve uptake and increase availability thereby helping children and young people to maximise their full health potential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews will be held on15th December 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameVeronique BlackJob titleOperational Lead for School Nursing and ImmunisationsEmail addressveronique.black@nhs.netTelephone number020 8274 6443Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
